claim.claim-text:
The system of claim 1, wherein:
the rotary transformer (16) includes a primary tank circuit (16P) and a secondary tank circuit (16S);
the control unit includes:
a control unit digital processor (20);
a power wave generation circuit (22) controlled by the control unit digital processor (20) that produces the power signal and modulates the power signal based on the control unit data;
the sensor assembly (14;14A) includes:
a sensor (52) for sensing the parameter;
a sensor assembly digital processor (40) for producing sensor data representative of the parameter sensed by the sensor (52);
a power regulation circuit (42) connected to the secondary tank circuit (16S) to provide electric power for the sensor assembly (14;14A) derived from the power signal;
a demodulation circuit (63;63A) electrically connected to the secondary tank circuit (16S) for demodulating the power signal to provide the control unit data to the sensor assembly digital processor (40); and
a load modulation circuit (56) connected to the secondary tank circuit (16S) to produce a load modulation signal based on the sensor data.

A method of simultaneously providing both power and control unit data from a control unit to a sensor assembly (14;14A), the method comprising:
generating control unit data;
generating a power signal having a carrier frequency;
modulating the power signal according to the control unit data to encode the control unit data in the waveform;
transmitting the power signal across a rotary transformer (16);
receiving the power signal at the sensor assembly (14;14A) from the rotary transformer (16);
deriving electric power for the sensor assembly (14;14A) from the power signal; and
demodulating the power signal to derive the control unit data at the sensor assembly (14;14A).

The method of claim 10, 11 or 12, and further comprising:
sensing a parameter;
producing sensor data representative of the parameter sensed;
load modulating the power signal based on the sensor data at the sensor assembly (14;14A); and
load demodulating the power signal at the control unit to derive the sensor data.
